<item>
            <title>[WFLY-6728] JDBC persistence-store for Artemis</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFLY-6728</link>
                <project id="12313721" key="WFLY">WildFly</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Apache ActiveMQ had the capability to store messages into a database via JDBC. In Apache ActiveMQ Artemis this has gone.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For a consistent backup data of various (co-located) systems participating in transactions should reside at the same datastore as otherwise this needs to be achieved through application software design (i.e. idempotent consumers etc.).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As in Apache ActiveMQ Artemis a JDBC Persistence-Store is about to be introduced we should also offer this capability on WildFly / EAP.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
